  "prompt": "What are some ways to restore a Compaq computer to factory settings?",
  "response": "Restoring a Compaq computer to factory settings can vary depending on the model and operating system it uses. Below are general methods for different scenarios:\n\n### **For Windows 10 or 11:**\n1. **Using Built-in Recovery Option:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Update & Security** > **Recovery**.\n   - Under **Reset this PC**, click **Get started**.\n   - Choose **Remove everything** to restore the computer to factory settings.\n\n2. **Using Recovery Partition:**\n   - Restart the computer.\n   - During startup, repeatedly press the **F11** key (for Compaq computers) to access the **Recovery Manager**.\n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to restore the computer to factory settings.\n\n3. **Using Installation Media:**\n   - Create a bootable USB or DVD with the Windows installation media.\n   - Boot the computer from the USB/DVD and follow the prompts to reinstall Windows.\n\n---\n\n### **For Older Windows Versions (e.g., Windows 7 or 8):**\n1. **Using Recovery Manager:**\n   - Restart the computer and press **F11** during startup to access the Recovery Manager.\n   - Select **System Recovery** or **Factory Reset** and follow the on-screen instructions.\n\n2. **Using Recovery Discs:**\n   - If you have recovery discs created earlier, insert the first disc and restart the computer.\n   - Follow the prompts to restore the system.\n\n---\n\n### **General Tips:**\n- **Backup Data:** Before restoring to factory settings, back up all important files, as the process will erase all data.\n- **Power Source:** Ensure the computer is plugged into a power source during the process to avoid interruptions.\n- **Product Key:** Have your Windows product key handy if required during reinstallation.\n\nIf the above methods don\u2019t work, consult the [Compaq/HP support website](https://support.hp.com) for model-specific instructions or contact HP customer support.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
